          "text" : "7 Segment Decoder",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "See ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Semiconductor-Diodes#7-Segment-Display",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " for more details on 7-segment displays.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We use a BCD to 7-segment decoder IC, such as the 7447, to convert BCD to a signal that can be displayed on a 7-segment",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "display. The 7447 has 4 inputs, A-D, and 7 outputs, a-g. The outputs are connected to the 7-segment display, and the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "inputs are connected to the BCD output of the microcontroller.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
